# Console completo com observabilidade

## 1) Objetivo
Padronizar apps console completos para integrações batch, com resiliencia (Polly), mensageria opcional e observabilidade.

## 2) Estrutura de pastas
```
src/
  App/
    Program.cs
    Jobs/
    Pipelines/
  Application/
    Services/
    DTOs/Validators/
  Domain/
    Entities/
  Infrastructure/
    Messaging/
    Observability/
    Storage/
deploy/
  Dockerfile
tests/
  Unit/
  Integration/
```

## 3) Pacotes recomendados
- Serilog.Extensions.Hosting, Serilog.Sinks.Console
- OpenTelemetry.Extensions.Hosting
- OpenTelemetry.Instrumentation.Http
- OpenTelemetry.Exporter.OpenTelemetryProtocol
- MediatR
- Polly, Polly.Contrib.WaitAndRetry
- MassTransit (Kafka ou RabbitMQ) quando houver fila

## 4) Configuracao (Program.cs)
```csharp
Host.CreateDefaultBuilder(args)
    .UseSerilog((ctx, cfg) => cfg.ReadFrom.Configuration(ctx.Configuration))
    .ConfigureServices((ctx, services) =>
    {
        services.AddMediatR(cfg => cfg.RegisterServicesFromAssemblyContaining<Program>());
        services.AddOpenTelemetry()
            .WithTracing(t => t.AddHttpClientInstrumentation().AddSource("BatchJobs"))
            .WithMetrics(m => m.AddRuntimeInstrumentation());

        services.AddHttpClient("legacy", c => c.BaseAddress = new Uri(ctx.Configuration["Legacy:BaseUrl"]!))
            .AddPolicyHandler(Policy.TimeoutAsync<HttpResponseMessage>(TimeSpan.FromSeconds(10)))
            .AddPolicyHandler(Policy<HttpResponseMessage>.Handle<HttpRequestException>().WaitAndRetryAsync(3, Polly.Contrib.WaitAndRetry.Backoff.DecorrelatedJitterBackoffV2(TimeSpan.FromSeconds(1), 3)));

        services.AddHostedService<ImportPipelineJob>();
    })
    .Build()
    .Run();
```

## 5) Exemplo de pipeline com steps
```csharp
public class ImportPipelineJob : BackgroundService
{
    private readonly ILogger<ImportPipelineJob> _logger;
    private readonly IMediator _mediator;
    public ImportPipelineJob(ILogger<ImportPipelineJob> logger, IMediator mediator)
    {
        _logger = logger; _mediator = mediator;
    }

    protected override async Task ExecuteAsync(CancellationToken stoppingToken)
    {
        _logger.LogInformation("Starting import pipeline");
        await _mediator.Send(new FetchLegacyDataCommand(), stoppingToken);
        await _mediator.Send(new NormalizeDataCommand(), stoppingToken);
        await _mediator.Send(new PersistDataCommand(), stoppingToken);
        _logger.LogInformation("Import pipeline completed");
    }
}
```

## 6) Observabilidade
- Logs estruturados com spans por etapa do pipeline.
- Traces para chamadas HTTP/DB e spans manuais por etapa.
- Metrics: tempo por etapa, contagem de registros processados, erros.

## 7) Resiliencia
- Polly: timeout + retry com jitter para chamadas externas.
- Controle de idempotencia (marcadores de lote) para evitar reprocessamento.
- Dead-letter ou re-drive para mensagens/arquivos com erro (quando usar fila).

## 8) Dockerfile (opcional)
```Dockerfile
FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/runtime:9.0 AS base
WORKDIR /app

FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:9.0 AS build
WORKDIR /src
COPY . .
RUN dotnet restore ./src/App/App.csproj
RUN dotnet publish ./src/App/App.csproj -c Release -o /app/publish

FROM base AS final
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=build /app/publish .
ENTRYPOINT ["dotnet", "App.dll"]
```

## 9) Testes
- Unit: steps/pipelines e validadores.
- Integration: execucao end-to-end contra APIs legadas mockadas (WireMock) e armazenamento real/containers.

## 10) Checklist
- Observabilidade ativa (logs + traces + metrics) por etapa.
- Resiliencia configurada em IO externo.
- Pipelines cobertos por testes unitarios e de integracao.
- Dockerfile pronto para empacotar o job.
